<content type="str">Arsenal and United in Griezmann battle 
The Mail on Sunday believes that Manchester United and Arsenal will battle it out for the signing of Atletico Madrid forward Antoine Griezmann . Arsenal made an approach for the player in the summer, but will try again at the end of the season. United are believed to be in pole position given their ability to pay higher wages, and his friendship with Manchester United midfielder Paul Pogba . Griezmann would cost around £85 million. 
Tweet 
Paper Round&apos;s view: Manchester United also had interest in Griezmann the season before last, so he has been a target for at least two years now. United have been mentioned as a destination for most of the season, and have the ability to spend money far easier than Arsenal do. While they also have Pogba, it might be that Champions League football is what makes the final decision on his next club. 

