Klopp on the ropes after Wolves defeat 
After a week that saw them lose 3-2 at home to Swansea , knocked out of the League Cup against Southampton and then the FA Cup with an embarrassing defeat to Wolves, the Star says that Liverpool boss Jurgen Klopp is on the ropes, as he admits the defeat was his fault. There is now only the league to focus on, but their next match is against Chelsea . 
Tweet 
Paper Round&apos;s view: The Anfield crowd - see Brendan Rodgers and Roy Hodgson - will turn on managers quicker than is generally believed. While Klopp still has Liverpool fans&apos; support, their patience is not to be tested. Klopp urgently needs to fix out the mediocre squad and buy some competent defenders before the end of the transfer window, and get Sadio Mane back as quickly as possible. Otherwise this wobble could turn into a slip down the table. 

